      • fromPlayer

        public static ViewPlayer fromPlayer​(Player player)
        Convert a regular Player to a simplified ViewPlayer Damages and marks are represented by Strings instead of other ViewPlayers to prevent infinite recursion of this method. The other way could be possible by creating all ViewPlayers and then setting damages and marks to them.
        Parameters:
        player - original Player
        Returns:
        converted player

      • fromAcceptableTypes

        public static SelectableOptionsWrapper fromAcceptableTypes​(AcceptableTypes acceptableTypes)
        Gets a selectableOptionsWrapper from AcceptableTypes. It supports the conversion of:
      • Action to string
      • Effect to string
      • List of players to list of string
      • List of powerups to list of ViewPowerUp
      • List of tiles to list of ViewTileCoords
      • Direction to string
      • Ammo to string
      • Weapon to string
        • It saves the same receiving type.
Parameters:
acceptableTypes - to be converted
Returns:
selectableOptionsWrapper equal to the acceptableTypes
